  <title>Flux and Surface Integrals (FS)</title>

  <objectives>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        This module develops the idea of a flux integral and a surface integral, and culminates in Stokes' Theorem and the Divergence Theorem- methods of computing flux/surface integrals using simpler multiple integrals. 
      </p>
    </introduction>
      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>FS1</title>
          <p>
            Given a vector field, I can compute its divergence and curl, and interpret my results.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>FS2</title>
          <p>
            I can compute the surface area of a parametrized surface.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>FS3</title>
          <p>
            I can compute surface integrals of a scalar function and a vector field, and interpret my answers.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>FS4</title>
          <p>
            I can use Stokesâ€™ Theorem and the Divergence Theorem to evaluate various mathematical expressions, and interpret my answers.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
  </objectives>
  
